      "side": 1,
      "message": "[🟡 Suggestion] Line 1779: The debounce only coalesces calls until the first timer fires; once the timer fires, every later call teardown schedules another malloc_trim(). In workloads with frequent short calls this can run malloc_trim() repeatedly every few seconds, and malloc_trim() walks arenas and takes allocator locks, so it can become a recurring process-wide latency source. Consider tracking whether a trim is already pending/running and enforcing a minimum interval between trims, or only scheduling when the last active call is removed.",
      "revId": "aec32800fe7f964911f8ee6b15b2bb74d7039bf1",
      "serverId": "1e26b4c1-6b8c-47ff-9df7-501b633d3b5a"
